content.description: Climb the slightly overhanging crack.  Crux involves a big move from a good side pull up to a horizontal crack.
content.protection: A couple of crash pads and a spotter or two.
content.location:
On the "backside" of the Equinox boulder.

From the East forest parking walk along the trail towards the West forest just inside the the forest, this boulder sits on the edge of the clear cut and forest in a cluster of big boulders. It is about 50 yards East of the West Forest Arete

content.description: Pure power climbing at its best.
content.location: Located on the obvious overhanging arete on the southeast end of the Equinox boulder. Start low on the right side of the arete with a incut sidepull for your right hand. Fire up the steep arete finishing on the left side. Be careful on the slab above!

content.description: Traverse right on a slopey edge onto jugs before a long reach at the lip. Awesome Problem!
content.location: In the west forest parking area.  The next boulder to the east of the ?West Forest Arete? boulder.  The boulder is right on the clearcut-forest boundary and the problem is on the west face.

content.description: Sart low on nice left crimp and bad right crimp.  Head up to nice flake and then traverse left on rail to top.  Fantastic problem with great moves.
content.location:
In the west forest parking area.  The next boulder to the east of the ?West Forest Arete? boulder.  On the Equinox boulder, same as

Summer Solstice V3-V4

.  The problem is on the south face.

content.description: Start low on nice big ledge.  Head straight up the finger crack and topout.
content.location:
In west forest parking area.  Just 5 feet left of

V3 Crack?

on same boulder.
The next boulder east of the West Forest Arete boulder, and right behind (north) the Equinox boulder; on the east face of the boulder

content.description: SDS on sloper and head up with the left hand to crappy sloper. Then get your left heel on the start hold and go up with your right hand to another crappy crimper/sloper by your left hand.  Then make a large move to the left to large jug and top out.  A Gold Bar Classic!
content.location:
In the west forest just to the right of

Equinox Boulder V3

.  The Equinox boulder is technically in the clearcut but right on the clearcut/forest boundary.
